igh, hence under conditions of host sympatry, it was confined to the preferred host only. However, under conditions of host allopatry, it utilized both hosts. There appears to be an increasing prevalence in host preferences of the parasites toward confinement to a single host species. The ecological isolation of the bat hosts and a long history of host\u2013parasite co-existence could have contributed to an overall tendency of bat ectoparasites to become specialists, here reflected in the high percentage of monoxeny.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Seneviratne, Sampath S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fernando, H. Chandrika", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Udagama-Randeniya, Preethi V.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/6540cbb4da99dede169e7c34d3ffe84e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/2496603a09d16d31f2767c6dfb71bf0e5ca5cc104be85ea2fd23982276112d92", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/D4YNV5EG", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/D4YNV5EG", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/e535acab10be3eb5d9c6a6e65c892f55!/b309067-311542", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/26f7ce5dd404e33c6570edd4ba250d20", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "9", "pages": "995-1002", "title": "International Jour